spokesperson%20for%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Fisheries%20and%20Aquatic%20Resources%2C%20said%20on%20Saturday%2C%20per%20a%20translation%20from%20Filipino%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philstar.com%2Fheadlines%2F2024%2F02%2F17%2F2334104%2Fchina-using-cyanide-destroy-scarborough-purpose-bfar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Philippine%20Star.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwwf.panda.org%2Fwwf_news%2F%3F5563%2FCyanide-an-easy-but-deadly-way-to-catch-fish%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECyanide%20fishing%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20controversial%20fishing%20method%20that%20typically%20involves%20dumping%20the%20highly%20toxic%20chemical%20near%20coral%20reefs%20or%20in%20fishing%20grounds%20to%20stun%20or%20kill%20fish%20so%20they%20can%20be%20easily%20captured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20widely%20condemned%20because%20it%20indiscriminately%20affects%20most%20marine%20species%20in%20the%20area%2C%20causes%20severe%20damage%20to%20aquatic%20ecosystems%2C%20and%20can%20make%20fish%20harmful%20to%20handle%20or%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Brigeura%20accused%20the%20Chinese%20fishermen%20of%20using%20cyanide%20to%20also%20%26quot%3Bintentionally%20destroy%20Bajo%20de%20Masinloc%20to%20prevent%20Filipino%20fishing%20boats%20to%20fish%20in%20the%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20The%20Philippine%20Star.%20Bajo%20de%20Masinloc%20is%20the%20Spanish%20name%20for%20the%20Scarborough%20Shoal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20estimated%20that%20the%20alleged%20use%20of%20cyanide%20would%20result%20in%20around%20%2417%2C850%2C000%20in%20damages%20to%20the%20region%2C%20per%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bureau%20said%20it%20has%20not%20conducted%20a%20formal%20study%20of%20the%20total%20damage%2C%20but%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20The%20Philippine%20Star%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225588%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20photo%20taken%20on%20February%2015%2C%202024%2C%20shows%20an%20aerial%20view%20of%20Scarborough%20Shoal%20in%20the%20disputed%20South%20China%20Sea.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d2f1faa610a9069d5a565a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223717%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20photo%20taken%20on%20February%2015%2C%202024%2C%20shows%20an%20aerial%20view%20of%20Scarborough%20Shoal%20in%20the%20disputed%20South%20China%20Sea.%3Cp%3EJAM%20STA%20ROSA%2FAFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20see%20clearer%2C%20and%20we%20will%20have%20proof%20or%20evidence%20that%20this%20is%20really%20being%20done%20by%20Chinese%20fishermen%20and%2C%20apparently%2C%20other%20foreign%20fishers%2C%26quot%3B%20Briguera%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gmanetwork.com%2Fnews%2Ftopstories%2Fnation%2F897865%2Fchinese-coast-guard-removes-barrier-at-bajo-de-masinloc-but-encounters-continue%2Fstory%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Philippine%20outlet%20GMA%20News.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Philippine%20Coast%20Guard%20on%20Sunday%20said%20it%20hadn't%20found%20any%20evidence%20of%20Chinese%20fishermen%20using%20cyanide%20and%20could%20not%20confirm%20the%20fisheries%20bureau's%20accusation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20any%20scientific%20study%20or%20any%20evidence%20that%20would%20suggest%20that%20cyanide%20fishing%20in%20Bajo%20de%20Masinloc%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20the%20Chinese%20or%20the%20Vietnamese%20fishermen%2C%26quot%3B%20coast%20guard%20spokesperson%20spokesperson%20Commodore%20Jay%20Tarriela%20said%2C%20per%20GMA%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20Philippines'%20fishing%20industry%20was%20known%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wri.org%2Fdata%2Fdestructive-fishing-widespread-southeast-asia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20cyanide%20fishing%20back%20in%20the%201960s%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20capture%20live%20fish%20for%20aquariums%20and%20restaurants%2C%20though%20the