7%20years%20died%20unexpectedly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20family%20had%20lived%20as%20expats%20in%20six%20countries%20and%20raised%20their%20teenage%20daughter%20in%20Spain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMadrid%20supported%20her%20when%20she%20felt%20lonely%20back%20then%2C%20so%20she%20relocated%20there%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%20If%20there's%20one%20rule%20grief%20counselors%20and%20bereavement%20support%20groups%20agree%20on%2C%20it's%20that%20making%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-how-long-soon-date-after-death-of-spouse-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebig%20decision%20following%20a%20loss%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20a%20good%20idea.%20Whether%20it's%20changing%20jobs%2C%20discarding%20keepsakes%2C%20or%20selling%20your%20home%20and%20moving%2C%20the%20general%20advice%20is%20to%20wait%20from%20six%20months%20to%20a%20year%20before%20embarking%20on%20a%20path%20that%20could%20be%20life-altering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20of%2027%20years%20died%2C%20I%20completely%20disregarded%20that%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20died%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20having%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20a%20rare%20lymphoma%2014%20months%20earlier%20and%20then%20medically%20evacuated%20from%20an%20assignment%20in%20Greece.%20We%20spent%20that%20year%20of%20his%20treatment%20living%20out%20of%20suitcases%20in%20a%20temporary%20apartment%20and%20dreaming%20of%20returning%20to%20post%20once%20the%20nightmare%20was%20over.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20his%20cancer%20relapsed%20for%20the%20third%20time%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20discontinue%20the%20treatment.%20His%20death%2C%20a%20mere%20three%20weeks%20later%2C%20didn't%20only%20leave%20me%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-helped-children-through-grief-losing-father-parenthood-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidow%20at%20an%20age%20I%20never%20imagined%20possible%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20it%20also%20meant%20that%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20losing%20a%20loved%20one%2C%20I%20lost%20my%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWidowhood%20and%20no%20place%20to%20call%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-quit-job-expat-move-abroad-qatar-singapore-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobe-trotting%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%2025%20years%20and%20never%20in%20one%20place%20for%20long%20enough%20to%20sprout%20roots%2C%20home%20meant%20wherever%20my%20husband%2C%20daughter%2C%20and%20I%20were%20together.%20But%2C%20now%20that%20he%20was%20gone%20and%20my%20daughter%20was%20grown%2C%20I%20was%20faced%20with%20a%20realization%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20planning%20a%20funeral%2C%20I%20also%20had%20to%20make%20a%20major%20decision.%20Where%20was%20I%20going%20to%20live%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20our%20expat%20career%2C%20we%20lived%20and%20worked%20in%20six%20countries%20and%20traveled%20to%20over%2040%20more.%20Yet%20one%20country%20%E2%80%94%20and%20particularly%20one%20city%20%E2%80%94%20had%20always%20captured%20our%20affections%20enough%20to%20discuss%20returning%20there%20to%20retire.%20For%20me%2C%20though%2C%20Madrid%20wasn't%20only%20a%20wonderfully%20livable%20city%20with%20cultural%20activities%20galore%2C%20excellent%20public%20transport%2C%20and%20amounts%20of%20sunshine%20to%20rival%20Florida.%20The%20last%20time%20we'd%20lived%20there%2C%20the%20city%20had%20helped%20pull%20me%20out%20of%20desperation%20so%20deep%20it%20seemed%20unsurmountable.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20perfect%20city%20for%20the%20lonely%20and%20sad%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221834%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20women%20seated%20at%20a%20yellow%20table%20in%20Madrid%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d2c48da3bd891424f85464%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221376%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMargarita%20Gokun%20Silver%20celebrated%20her%20birthday%20with%20her%20daughter%20in%20Madrid.%3Cp%3EMargarita%20Gokun%20Silver%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%202012%20to%202017%20stint%20in%20Madrid%20coincided%20with%20our%20daughter's%20rising%20adolescence.%20Several%20months%20shy%20of%20her%2013th%20birthday%2C%20she%20wasn't%20officially%20a%20teen%2C%20yet%2C%20unofficially%2C%20she%20exhibited%20all%20the%20signs.%20She%20slammed%20doors%2C%20screamed%20her%20way%20through%20arguments%2C%20and%20smeared%20ketchup%20on%20pads%20to%20impersonate%20a%20period%20so%20she%20could%20skip%20her%20swimming%20lessons.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20fought%20every%20day%20and%20our%20arguments%20always%20ended%20the%20same%20way%3A%20me%20on%20the%20kitchen%20floor%20crying%20and%20her%20in%20her%20room%20boiling%20with%20rage%20and%20messaging%20her%20friends.%20New%20in%20an%20unfamiliar%20city%20with%20a%20husband%20who%20was%20overwhelmed%20at%20work%2C%20I%20felt%20lonely%20and%20abandoned.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20outside%20my%20window%2C%20Madrid%20pulsed%20with%20the%20sounds%20of%20people%20having%20drinks%20with%20friends%2C%20chatting%20with%20vendors%20at%20the%20fruit%20stand%20across%20the%20street%2C%20and%20meeting%20neighbors%20at%20wine%20tastings%20in%20a%20delicatessen%20below.%20Mothers%20walked%20hand-in-hand%20with%20their%20teenage%20daughters%2C%20and%20whole%20families%20window-shopped%20as%20one.%20Togetherness%20defined%20this%20city%2C%20and%20yet%20I%20was%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20one%20day%2C%20after%20a%20particularly%20nasty%20fight%2C%20I%20was%20so%20desperate%20to%20be%20out%20of%20the%20house%20that%20I%20lingered%20at%20my%20neighborhood%20market.%20I%20elicited%20the%20fishmonger's%20advice%2C%20I%20asked%20the%20fruit%20vendor%20to%20help%20me%20choose%20the%20best%20tomatoes%2C%20and%2C%20at%20the%20bakery%2C%20the%20baker%20suggested%20I%20try%20a%20Galician%20loaf.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20in%20what%20seemed%20like%20an%20eternity%2C%20I%20was%20having%20conversations%20without%20hostility%20and%20resentment.%20People%20