imented%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20my%20time%20in%20national%20service%20was%20a%20transformative%20experience.%20As%20a%20military%20officer%2C%20I%20trained%20new%20conscripts%20during%20their%20basic%20military%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20found%20purpose%20and%20meaning%20in%20my%20role%20as%20military%20personnel%20and%20wanted%20to%20stay%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20kept%20me%20on%20the%20job%20was%20the%20camaraderie%20and%20friendships%20I%20forged%20with%20my%20superiors%2C%20peers%2C%20and%20subordinates.%20I%20felt%20that%20the%20strong%20bond%20between%20soldiers%20couldn't%20be%20found%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20the%20difficult%20decision%20to%20leave%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22856%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jianhui%20Tan%20(right)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ba0857ac2de4f17ee613a8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22795%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETan%20(rightmost)%20decided%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20with%20the%20SAF%20because%20he%20enjoyed%20his%20national%20service.%3Cp%3EJianhui%20Tan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20one's%20priorities%20do%20change.%20After%20spending%20about%2010%20years%20with%20the%20SAF%2C%20I%20got%20a%20wake-up%20call%20when%20my%20aunt%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20I%20hadn't%20been%20spending%20enough%20time%20with%20my%20family.%20I%20worked%20very%20long%20hours%20and%20stayed%20in%20the%20camps%20most%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20my%20family%20supported%20my%20decision%2C%20they%20warned%20me%20that%20life%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20would%20be%20very%20different%20from%20the%20military.%20My%20current%20and%20former%20bosses%20also%20discouraged%20me%20from%20leaving%2C%20citing%20the%20great%20career%20progression%20I%20could%20enjoy%20if%20I%20stayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20pressed%20on%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESwitching%20careers%20was%20tough%20and%20stressful%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221011%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jianhui%20Tan%20(center)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ba08db7a3d271488760db0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22991%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETan%20(center)%20left%20the%20SAF%20in%202021.%20He%20spent%20about%20six%20months%20taking%20courses%20and%20job-hunting%20before%20landing%20a%20job%20with%20Euromonitor.%3Cp%3EJianhui%20Tan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20left%20the%20SAF%20with%20no%20job%20offers%20on%20hand%2C%20and%20my%20career%20transition%20journey%20was%20stressful.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20when%20I%20would%20find%20a%20job.%20It%20also%20meant%20that%20I%20would%20not%20draw%20any%20income%20while%20job-hunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20relied%20on%20my%20savings%20while%20looking%20for%20work%20and%20spent%20around%20six%20months%20taking%20courses%20to%20get%20new%20certifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20last%20role%20in%20the%20military%20had%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20project%20management%2C%20so%20I%20took%20up%20courses%20to%20advance%20my%20skills%20in%20that%20area%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20I%20also%20dabbled%20in%20business%20intelligence%20courses%20because%20I%20enjoy%20working%20with%20numbers.%20The%20courses%20gave%20me%20a%20glimpse%20of%20what%20different%20industries%20were%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20trying%20to%20break%20into%20the%20private%20sector%20was%20daunting.%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20craft%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20based%20on%20my%20work%20experience%20in%20the%20army.%20There%20were%20things%20I%20couldn't%20include%20because%20of%20security%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20noticed%20by%20recruiters%20was%20also%20a%20challenge.%20Even%20when%20I%20was%20fortunate%20to%20be%20called%20up%2C%20I%20had%20to%20battle%20the%20stereotypes%20some%20people%20held%20toward%20military%20personnel.%20Some%20hirers%20had%20the%20false%20preconception%20that%20former%20soldiers%20had%20no%20relevant%20experience%20or%20could%20be%20rigid%20in%20their%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20I%20landed%20a%20job%20with%20the%20market%20research%20company%20Euromonitor%20as%20a%20business%20development%20account%20manager.%20I%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20met%20recruiters%20who%20believed%20that%20my%20past%20experiences%20were%20relevant%20and%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20chance%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGetting%20used%20to%20the%20corporate%20world%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20differences%20between%20the%20military%20and%20the%20private%20sector%20was%20the%20culture.%20In%20the%20army%2C%20there%20was%20brotherhood%20and%20camaraderie%2C%20and%20we%20were%20driven%20by%20a%20collective%20sense%20of%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20wasn't%20the%20case%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20where%20organizational%20bonding%20isn't%20as%20strong%20as%20it%20is%20in%20the%20military.%20It%20took%20me%20some%20time%20to%20get%20used%20to%20the%20new%20work%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntering%20a%20fresh%20industry%20meant%20that%20I%20had%20to%20navigate%20a%20steep%20learning%20curve.%20I%20had%20to%20learn%20a%20lot%20of%20new%20things%20in%20my%20first%20month%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20of%20course%2C%20I%20had%20to%20start%20thinking%20of%20what%20I%20should%20wear%20to%20work%20since%20I%20wasn't%20donning%20my%20army%20uniform%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20transition%20was%20tough%2C%20I%20also%20tapped%20on%20what%20I%20learned%20in%20the%20military%20to%20address%20the%20new%20challenges%20I%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20things%20I%20picked%20up%20in%20the%20army%20was%20how%20to%20communicate%20with%20and%20persuade%20people%20efficiently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20officer%2C%20I%20had%20to%20lead%20and%20influence%20some%20of%20my%20conscripts.%20I%20had%20to%20convince%20people%20to%20do%20things%20they%20didn't%20want%20to%20do.%20While%20conscripts%20had%20to%20obey%20orders%20because%20of%20military%20law%2C%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20important%20to%20win%20their%20trust%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20in%20the%20military%20also%20came%20with%20its%20own%20challenges%2C%20and%20it%20toughened%20me%20up%20and%20honed%20my%20resilience.%20That's%20why%20I%20don't%20shy%20away%20from%20new%20challenges%20that%20come%20my%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20have%20no%20regrets%20about%20starting%20my%20career%20with%20the%20SAF.%20The%20time%20I%20spent%20as%20a%20soldier%20made%20me%20a%20stronger%20and%20better%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-military-with-no-job-offers-transition-was-tough-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708299721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b9ed31ac2de4f17ee612a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-military-with-no-job-offers-transition-was-tough-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jianhui%20Tan%2C%2033%2C%20served%20in%20the%20Singapore%20Armed%20Forces%20for%2010%20years.%20He%20left%20the%20military%20to%20join%20the%20private%20sector%20in%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-military-with-no-job-offers-transition-was-tough-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20broke%20Chinese%20real%20estate%20developer%20left%20Los%20Angeles%20with%20empty%2C%20graffiti-covered%20towers%20and%20a%20billion-dollar%20bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%2227%20Floors%20Of%20Unfinished%20L.A.%20Luxury%20Skyscraper%20Tagged%20With%20Graffiti%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d037276fc