rth-system%20%E2%80%93%20how%20our%20planet%20has%20shaped%20us%20as%20human%20beings%2C%20and%20how%20we%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20have%20shaped%20it.%20Read%20the%20series%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fearths-changing-climate%5C%22%3EPart%201%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-planetary-perspective%5C%22%3EPart%202%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFire%20looms%20large%20in%20the%20ancient%20myths%20of%20many%20peoples%20around%20the%20world.%20Interestingly%2C%20most%20of%20these%20old%20stories%20share%20a%20common%20motif%2C%20in%20which%20fire%20was%20withheld%20from%20humankind%E2%80%94either%20by%20gods%20or%20by%20some%20other%20being%E2%80%94until%20humans%20finally%20acquired%20it%20only%20through%20an%20act%20of%20theft%2C%20violence%2C%20or%20other%20ignoble%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20tale%20from%20ancient%20Greece%2C%20the%20god%20Prometheus%20steals%20fire%20from%20his%20fellow%20gods%20to%20share%20it%20with%20humans%3B%20for%20this%20transgression%2C%20the%20other%20gods%20condemn%20him%20to%20endure%20an%20eternity%20of%20torture.%20The%20Polynesian%20demigod%2C%20Maui%20the%20trickster%2C%20ventures%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20world%20to%20retrieve%20fire%20from%20his%20grandmother%20Pele%2C%20the%20god%20of%20fire%2C%20by%20taking%20her%20burning%20fingernails%20one%20by%20one%E2%80%94only%20to%20churlishly%20extinguish%20each%20one%3B%20Pele%20finally%20grows%20so%20angry%20with%20him%20that%20she%20sends%20fire%20chasing%20after%20him%20into%20the%20human%20world.%20In%20one%20Din%C3%A9%20(Navajo)%20story%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fteachersinstitute.yale.edu%2Fcurriculum%2Funits%2F1998%2F2%2F98.02.02%2F5%5C%22%3Efire%20god%3C%2Fa%3E%20hoards%20fire%20for%20himself%2C%20using%20it%20only%20to%20destroy%20things%2C%20until%20trickster%20Coyote%20steals%20some%20and%20gives%20it%20to%20humans.%20Among%20different%20Australian%20Aboriginal%20peoples%2C%20the%20origin%20of%20fire%20is%20placed%20with%20various%20animals%2C%20or%20sometimes%20human%20women%2C%20from%20whom%20it%20is%20forcibly%20taken%20through%20violence%20or%20trickery%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20then%20distributed%20among%20the%20trees%20of%20the%20land%2C%20from%20where%20anyone%20can%20recover%20it.%20The%20ancient%20Vedic%20and%20Zoroastrian%20traditions%20are%20a%20bit%20different%2C%20but%20the%20fire%20god%E2%80%94Agni%20or%20Atar%E2%80%94is%20both%20devourer%20and%20protector.%20As%20the%20light%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vyasaonline.com%2Fencyclopedia%2Fagni%2F%5C%22%3Eknowledge%20and%20acculturation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academia.edu%2F39553500%2FProto_Indo_European_Fire_Theft_Myth%5C%22%3EAgni%20too%20once%20hid%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20humans%2C%20before%20serving%20as%20an%20intermediary%20between%20humans%20and%20the%20gods%20of%20the%20Vedic%20pantheon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20288px)%2085vw%2C%20288px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22288%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20stories%20from%20every%20quarter%20of%20the%20planet%20engage%20with%20the%20mystery%20and%20power%20of%20fire%20in%20ways%20that%20we%20of%20industrial%20civilisation%20do%20not.%20They%20imagine%20fire%20as%20being%20of%20divine%20origin%20or%20imbued%20with%20some%20property%20fundamentally%20tied%20to%20our%20very%20humanity%2C%20the%20world%20we%20inhabit%2C%20or%20divinity.%20Without%20it%2C%20our%20human%20world%20is%20incomplete.%20Yet%20an%20ambivalence%20too%20surrounds%20fire%2C%20either%20through%20explicit%20acknowledgement%20of%20its%20dual%20nature%20as%20both%20benefactor%20and%20destroyer%20or%20an%20implicit%20association%20of%20it%20with%20an%20act%20of%20transgression%20or%20moral%20corruption.%20But%20we%20need%20it%2C%20the%20stories%20tell%20us%3B%20its%20power%20to%20cook%20food%20and%20to%20keep%20us%20warm%20enables%20our%20human%20existence.%20Our%20evolutionary%20story%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20very%20deeply%20bound%20up%20with%20fire.%20And%20though%20no%20living%20society%20can%20possibly%20retain%20a%20true%20memory%20of%20the%20origins%20of%20a%20bond%20forged%20millions%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20remarkable%20that%20a%20mythic%20awareness%20of%20its%20centrality%20to%20human%20societies%2C%20its%20powers%20and%20its%20dangers%2C%20remains%20alive%20among%20peoples%20who%20retain%20their%20cultural%20connection%20with%20a%20non-industrialised%20worldview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDirect%20human%20connection%20to%20fire%20began%20as%20global%20temperatures%20were%20dropping%20into%20the%20Pleistocene%20ice%20age.%20Our%20early%20hominid%20ancestors%20in%20Africa%20had%20left%20the%20forest%20canopies%2C%20where%20they%E2%80%99d%20enjoyed%20a%20diet%20of%20raw%20leaves%20and%20fruit%2C%20seeds%20and%20insects%2C%20to%20explore%20new%20ways%20of%20life%20on%20the%20expanding%20open%20savannas.%20Their%20grassland%20lifestyles%20favored%20evolution%20toward%20bipedalism%2C%20along%20with%20dextrous%20minds%20and%20hands%20able%20to%20sharpen%20rocks%20into%20cutting%20implements.%20They%20must%20have%20learned%20they%20could%20glean%20good%20food%20from%20the%20charred%20leavings%20of%20forest%20fires.%20This%20accidental%20cooking%20rendered%20some%20foods%20easier%20to%20eat%20and%20digest%2C%20enabling%20these%20hominids%20to%20enjoy%20nutritious%20foods%20they%20might%20not%20have%20eaten%20before%2C%20like%20the%20calorifically%20dense%20tubers%20and%20corms%20that%20grew%20underground.%20This%20meant%20their%20bodies%20could%20receive%20more%20nutrition%20from%20food%20while%20expending%20less%20energy%20in%20processing%20and%20digesting%20it%2C%20because%20fire%20effectively%20did%20some%20of%20that%20processing%20and%20digesting%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chem.fsu.edu%2Fchemlab%2Fchm1020c%2FLecture%252525207%2F01.php%5C%22%3EFire%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D_GLb0s-FfZU%5C%22%3Eunique%20to%20Earth%20as%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself.%20It%20erupts%20when%20substances%20made%20mostly%20of%20carbon%20and%20hydrogen%E2%80%94fuels%2C%20like%20wood%20or%20oil%2C%20ultimately%20created%20by%20some%20living%20thing%E2%80%94are%20combined%20with%20ambient%20oxygen%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reagent.co.uk%2Fblog%2Fchemistry-of-fire%2F%5C%22%3Erunaway%20oxidative%20chemical%20reaction%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20converts%20them%20primarily%20into%20carbon-dioxide%20and%20water.%20The%20heat%20given%20off%20by%20this%20reaction%20can%20keep%20us%20warm%20in%20the%20cold%20or%20drive%20reactions%20in%20other%20substances%2C%20like%20in%20the%20food%20we%20eat.%20High%20heat%20changes%20the%20properties%20of%20our%20food%20by%20neutralising%20poisons%20it%20contained%20in%20its%20raw%20state%20(tubers%20and%20beans%20can%20be%20toxic%20before%20cooking)%2C%20softening%20its%20hard%20parts%2C%20killing%20any%20pathogens%20within%20it%2C%20altering%20the%20structures%20of%20its%20proteins%2C%20and%20releasing%20nutrients%20for%20easier%20absorption%20by%20our%20guts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndaman%20Islanders%20once%20had%20many%20living%20stories%20about%20the%20origins%20of%20fire.%20According%20to%20English%20anthropologist%20A.R.%20Radcliffe-Brown%2C%20who%20attempted%20to%20record%20them%20as%20they%20were%20fast%20disappearing%20under%20colonisation%2C%20several%20stories%20credited%20an%20ancestral%20matriarch%20for%20inventing%20fire.%20Some%20say%20she%20struck%20a%20red%20stone%20against%20a%20pearl%20shell%20(which%20also%20stood%20for%20lightening)%2C%20then%20fed%20the%20fire%20with%20wood%20and%20fell%20asleep.%20While%20she%20slept%2C%20Sir%20Dove%20stole%20this%20fire%20for%20himself.%20He%20later%20distributed%20fire%20to%20every%20village.%20It%E2%80%99s%20uncanny%20how%20this%20story%20echoes%20others%20from%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20energy%20we%20take%20from%20fire%20is%20%3Cem%3Eextra-somatic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20meaning%20it%20comes%20from%20outside%20of%20our%20bodies%2C%20beyond%20the%20calories%20we%20ingest%20in%20our%20food.%20Thus%2C%20controlling%20fire%20allows%20us%20to%20%E2%80%98steal%E2%80%99%20the%20energy%20released%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fuel%20and%20add%20some%20of%20it%20to%20the%20energy%20we%20get%20from%20the%20food%20itself%2C%20effectively%20increasing%20the%20amount%20of%20energy%20we%20use%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%94both%20directly%2C%20in%20the%20energy%20of%20cooking%2C%20and%20indirectly%2C%20by%20enabling%20us%20to%20extract%20more%20food%20energy%20from%20the%20same%20environment%20through%20an%20expanded%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20take%20this%20for%20granted%2C%20but%20this%20is%20the%20magic%20of%20cooking.%20And%20it%20marked%20a%20fundamental%20transition%20in%20how%20our%20kind%20taps%20into%20the%20resources%20available%20in%20our%20ecosystems.%20It%20gave%20us%20a%20larger%20portion%20of%20energy%20from%20an%20environment%20we%20share%20with%20other%20creatures%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20depend%20entirely%20on%20energy%20from%20the%20food%20they%20eat%20to%20maintain%20their%20life%20functions.%20At%20some%20point%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2019%2Fnov%2F21%2Fwildfire-prescribed-burns-california-native-americans%5C%22%3Enobody%20knows%20when%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94human%20communities%20also%20began%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.org%2Fen-us%2Fmagazine%2Fmagazine-articles%2Findigenous-controlled-burns-california%2F%5C%22%3Epractice%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbandipur-mudumalay-wayanad-controlled-forest-fire-biomass%5C%22%3Econtrolled%20burns%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fsubjects%2Ffire%2Findigenous-fire-practices-shape-our-land.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520goal%2520of%2520this%2520prescribed%2Cpreceded%2520by%2520a%2520traditional%2520ceremony.%5C%22%3Eshape%20and%20maintain%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucdavis.edu%2Fnews%2Fcultural-burning-illuminated%5C%22%3Eecosystems%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.universityofcalifornia.edu%2Fnews%2Fhow-indigenous-practice-good-fire-can-help-our-forests-thrive%5C%22%3Ewidely%20beneficial%3C%2Fa%3E%20ways%2C%20perhaps%20not%20so%20unlike%20the%20way%20other%20animals%20are%20known%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findigenousknowledge.unimelb.edu.au%2Fcurriculum%2Fthemes%2Ffire%5C%22%3Eshape%20their%20ecosystems%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20building%20dams%20(beavers)%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20or%20maintaining%20waterholes%20(elephants).%20This%20became%20another%20way%20that%20humans%20actively%20co-created%20enriched%20environments%2C%20alongside%20other%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20living%20system%20uses%20(consumes)%20more%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20it%20grows%3B%20for%20early%20humans%2C%20their%20increased%20consumption%20of%20biomass%E2%80%94as%20fuel%20to%20make%20fire%20and%20as%20food%E2%80%94would%20have%20caused%20an%20increase%20in%20their%20population%20size.%20The%20local%20ecosystem%20had%20to%20adjust%2C%20accommodating%20more%20%3Cem%3EHomo%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20fewer%20of%20something%20else%E2%80%94most%20noticeably%2C%20perhaps%2C%20other%20directly%20competing%20species%2C%20like%20similar%20hominids%20who%20did%20not%20use%20fire.%20The%20use%20of%20fire%20increased%20the%20%3Cem%3Ecarrying%20capacity%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20landscape%20for%20%3Cem%3EH.%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94that%20is%2C%20the%20land%20could%20support%20larger%20populations%20of%20them%20living%20this%20way%20of%20life%20effectively%20forever%2C%20or%20at%20least%20until%20something%20else%20changed%20their%20environment.%20Perhaps%20no%20other%20animals%20have%20made%20such%20intensive%20and%20crafty%20use%20of%20extra-somatic%20energy%20as%20humans%E2%80%94nor%20become%20so%20existentially%20dependent%20upon%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20all.%20All%20the%20ease%20our%20ancestors%20gained%20by%20cooking%20favored%20the%20evolution%20of%20new%20body%20forms%20with%20smaller%20guts%20and%20teeth%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbigthink.com%2Fthe-present%2Finventions-fire%2F%5C%22%3Elarger%20brains%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Before%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20Pleistocene%20ice%20age%2C%20our%20ancestors%20controlled%20fire%20well%20enough%20to%20build%20cooking%20hearths.%20This%20suggests%20that%2C%20rather%20than%20eating%20on%20the%20spot%20whatever%20each%20one%20collected%20or%20killed%2C%20as%20most%20primates%20do%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faustralian.museum%2Flearn%2Fscience%2Fhuman-evolution%2Fhominid-and-hominin-whats-the-difference%2F%5C%22%3Ehominins%3C%2Fa%3E%20carried%20their%20day%E2%80%99s%20bounty%20back%20to%20their%20camp%2C%20threw%20it%20onto%20the%20fire%2C%20and%20then%20shared%20it%20with%20their%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20indigenous%20peoples%20around%20the%20world%2C%20some%20Adivasis%20once%20maintained%20their%20forest%20ecosystems%20by%20setting%20controlled%20fires.%20Such%20regular%20burns%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.survivalinternational.org%2Fnews%2F11939%5C%22%3Eprevented%20wildfires%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20during%20British%20Colonial%20times%2C%20when%20forests%20became%20widely%20perceived%20primarily%20as%20a%20source%20of%20timber%20and%20profit%2C%20the%20Adivasis%E2%80%99%20controlled%20burns%20were%20stopped.%20This%20is%20one%20reason%20why%20wildfires%20have%20become%20a%20growing%20threat%20in%20India%2C%20more%20so%20under%20the%20rising%20heat%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitting%20around%20the%20hearth%2C%20distributing%20food%2C%20contesting%20over%20what%20was%20fair%20and%20who%20owed%20what%20to%20whom%2C%20suffering%20harassment%20by%20the%20greedy%20meanies%E2%80%94or%20collectively%20harassing%20them%20in%20retribution%E2%80%94social%20pressures%20favored%20evolution%20toward%20increasing%20capacities%20to%20understand%20and%20utter%20vocalisations%20that%20coded%20for%20more%20complex%20and%20nuanced%20information.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20enriched%20imaginative%20powers%20that%20could%20project%20one%20person%20into%20another%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%2C%20able%20to%20visualize%20and%20contemplate%20encounters%20and%20experiences%20known%20only%20through%20gestural%20and%20vocal%20communication.%20Our%20hominin%20ancestors%20had%20already%20been%20teaching%20each%20other%20how%20to%20fashion%20tools%2C%20how%20to%20tend%20fire%2C%20perhaps%20even%20how%20to%20locate%20the%20best%20tubers%20or%20caches%20of%20nuts%20or%20honey.%20Maybe%2C%20in%20exchanging%20information%20about%20their%20environment%20by%20recounting%20their%20day%E2%80%99s%20exploits%2C%20they%20began%20to%20tell%20stories%20in%20language%20increasingly%20rich%20enough%20to%20build%20worlds%2C%20to%20articulate%20beliefs%20and%20rules%20about%20how%20to%20live%2C%20to%20profess%20their%20love%20or%20to%20complain%20about%20the%20resident%20bully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20while%20these%20earliest%20humans%20were%20developing%20cooking%20technologies%20that%20transformed%20their%20bodies%2C%20they%20were%20also%20growing%20into%20highly%20social%2C%20cooperative%20animals%20capable%20of%20teaching%20and%20learning%20from%20one%20another%20about%20their%20material%20and%20social%20worlds.%20Over%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20generations%20they%20accumulated%20this%20knowledge%2C%20passed%20it%20down%20from%20elders%20to%20youths%2C%20recounted%20it%20in%20tales%20told%20around%20the%20fire%2C%20listening%20to%20the%20sounds%20of%20the%20night%2C%20gazing%20up%20at%20a%20milky%20profusion%20of%20stars.%20From%20this%20they%20would%20weave%20threads%20upon%20threads%20of%20human%20stories%20into%20tapestries%20of%20meaning%2C%20eventually%20gathering%20these%20together%20and%20binding%20them%2C%20layer%20over%20layer%2C%20into%20all%20enveloping%20edifices%20of%20%3Cem%3Ehuman%20culture%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94an%20immersive%20environment%20of%20stories%2C%20a%20universe%20of%20interconnected%20notions%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20shared%20delusion%20that%20models%20for%20each%20community%20their%20shared%20meanings%20of%20life%2C%20how%20the%20cosmos%20works%2C%20what%20has%20value%2C%20what%20is%20their%20rightful%20place%20in%20the%20world%2C%20what%20possible%20futures%20lie%20before%20them%2C%20and%20much%20else%20besides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20culture%20is%20an%20awe-inspiring%20phenomenon%20that%20has%20long%20forged%20meaning%20and%20purpose%20in%20conversation%20with%20our%20deep%20awareness%20of%20the%20planet%E2%80%99s%20biophysical%20reality.%20However%E2%80%94as%20future%20essays%20in%20this%20series%20will%20describe%E2%80%94in%20modern%2C%20industrial%20societies%2C%20the%20tether%20between%20culture%20and%20biophysical%20reality%20has%20become%20increasingly%20frayed%3B%20our%20modern%20culture%20has%20now%20become%20a%20self-referential%20bubble%2C%20adrift%20from%20our%20planet%E2%80%99s%20own%20life%20and%20rhythms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20early%20ancestors%20first%20learned%20to%20control%20fire%2C%20the%20ecological%20shift%20was%20apparently%20gradual.%20It%20remained%20sustainable%20for%20well%20over%20a%20million%20years%2C%20even%20as%20it%20increased%20human%20populations%20enough%20to%20spread%20out%20of%20Africa%20and%20establish%20themselves%20across%20ice-age%20Eurasia.%20Nevertheless%2C%20when%20humans%20entered%20those%20far-flung%20ecosystems%2C%20this%20would%20necessarily%20have%20destabilised%20them%20at%20first.%20It%20would%20have%20left%20them%20forever%20altered%20them%20forever%20by%20accommodating%20a%20new%20apex%20predator%E2%80%94human%20beings%E2%80%94on%20the%20local%20landscapes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20trove%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2666033423000266%5C%22%3Earchaic%20stone%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1040618220304754%5C%22%3Esites%20across%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20alongside%20a%20handful%20of%20early%20hominin%20fossils%20from%20the%20Narmada%20River%20basin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC378623%2F%5C%22%3Eand%20modern%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.wayne.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D2055%26context%3Dhumbiol%5C%22%3Egenetic%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20attest%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-020-14668-4%5C%22%3Econtinuous%20presence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fscience%2Fstone-tools-found-tamil-nadu-suggest-humans-left-africa-much-earlier%5C%22%3Emultiple%20human%20lineages%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20subcontinent%20since%20the%20dispersal%20of%20%3Cem%3E%20erectus%3C%2Fem%3E%20out%20of%20Africa.%20The%20oldest%20finds%2C%20unearthed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmart-news%2Fstone-tools-india-raise-questions-about-spread-ancient-technology-180968020%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DArchaeologists%2520at%2520the%2520Sharma%2520Center%2Cwith%2520the%2520Early%2520Stone%2520Age.%5C%22%3EAttirampakkam%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20simple%20stone%20tools%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2666033423000266%5C%22%3E1.5%20million%20years%20old%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20plausibility%20that%20different%20lineages%20intermixed%20over%20a%20thousand%20millennia%20suggests%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fscience%2Fstone-tools-found-tamil-nadu-suggest-humans-left-africa-much-earlier%5C%22%3Emajor%20crossroads%20for%20human%3C%2Fa%3E%20admixture%20and%20evolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20species%20that%20increases%20its%20number%20within%20an%20ecosystem%20ultimately%20changes%20the%20conditions%20for%20all%20other%20local%20species%2C%20because%20their%20enlarged%20presence%20changes%20the%20way%20that%20energy%20and%20materials%20flow%20through%20that%20ecosystem.%20But%20fluctuations%20of%20species%20within%20changing%20ecosystems%20are%20normal%20for%20living%20systems%2C%20which%20are%20never%20static.%20Disruptions%20and%20even%20occasional%20extinctions%20caused%20by%20the%20expansion%20of%20one%20species%20need%20not%20lead%20to%20total%20annihilation%20of%20ecosystems%20nor%20disintegration%20of%20the%20planet%E2%80%99s%20biogeochemical%20cycles.%20In%20fact%2C%20once%20an%20ecosystem%20establishes%20a%20new%20balance%20to%20accommodate%20a%20new%20species%2C%20it%20may%20ultimately%20become%20richer%20than%20it%20had%20been%20before.%20Such%20fluctuations%20are%20different%20from%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20large-scale%20ecosystem%20%3Cem%3Eannihilation%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20marks%20the%20Anthropocene%20and%20is%20only%20a%20recent%20development%2C%20not%20necessarily%20intrinsic%20to%20our%20human%20nature%20or%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20one%20has%20to%20wonder%20if%20the%20stories%20told%20by%20the%20first%20Australians%2C%20the%20Din%C3%A9%2C%20the%20Polynesians%2C%20and%20others%2C%20as%20they%20were%20expanding%20across%20the%20planet%20in%20their%20time%2C%20captured%20some%20unnamed%20awareness%20of%20the%20destabilization%20their%20presence%20brought%20to%20their%20new%20lands.%20Could%20that%20be%20one%20source%20of%20their%20stories%E2%80%99%20ambivalence%20about%20fire%3F%20Was%20it%20some%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20moral%20and%20existential%20dangers%20of%20mastering%20a%20force%20mightier%20than%20themselves%3F%20Of%20the%20disruptions%20they%20caused%20with%20its%20super-human%20power%3F%20The%20ancient%20stories%20may%20have%20reminded%20their%20audiences%20that%20wielding%20the%20power%20of%20fire%20entails%20responsibilities%2C%20obligating%20us%20into%20a%20system%20of%20mutual%20sharing%20and%20care%20for%20our%20environment%2C%20fundamentally%20tied%20to%20our%20own%20survival%E2%80%94a%20wisdom%20we%20have%20forgotten%20in%20our%20industrial%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20time%20I%E2%80%99ll%20look%20at%20the%20crucial%20role%20ice%20also%20plays%20in%20the%20human%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%3Cem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EOnly%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708241441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18113620%2F1620px-Bandipur_fires_2019.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-forged-by-fire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fire%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20as%20unique%20to%20Earth%20as%20life%20itself.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-forged-by-fire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20Union%20Govt%20Took%20a%20Big%20Step%20Towards%20NPR%2C%20NRC%20in%202015%20Without%20Informed%20Consent%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F22120239%2FMANUU.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ECitizen%E2%80%99s%20activism%20through%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20(RTI)%20has%20revealed%20how%2C%20a%20giant%20step%20towards%20NPR%20and%20NRC%20was%20taken%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20when%20the%20information%20contained%20in%20the%20Aadhaar%20database%20was%20linked%20with%20the%20NPR%20database%20in%202015.%20While%20the%20only%20legal%20way%20of%20linking%20the%20two%20databases%20is%20by%20acquiring%C2%A0%3Cb%3Einformed%20consent%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0from%20every%20resident%20through%20a%20public%20exercise%20similar%20to%20the%20Census%2C%20which%20means%20through%20a%20public%20exercise%20conducted%20by%20the%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%20(RGI)%2C%20investigations%20reveal%20that%20the%20exercise%20did%20not%20have%20any%20provision%20to%20collect%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eany%20informed%20consent%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Efor%20this%20linkage%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0This%20presentation%20below%2C%20exclusively%20available%20on%20CJP%20reveals%20that%20this%20apparently%20illegal%20action%20makes%20the%20NPR%20an%20even%20greater%20threat%20to%20the%20common%20people%20than%20what%20was%20previously%20thought.%20The%20involved%20citizens%20in%20and%20around%20Metiabruz%20Kolkata%20are%20close%20collaborators%20with%C2%A0%3Ci%3ECitizens%20for%20Justice%20and%20Peace%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E(cjp.org.in)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nationwide%20movement%20against%20the%20National%20Population%20Register%20(NPR)%20and%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%2C%20which%20was%20triggered%20by%20passing%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Bill%20(CAB)%2C%20came%20to%20an%20abrupt%20halt%20in%202020%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20Covid-19%2C%20the%20subsequent%20lockdown%20imposed%20by%20the%20government%20and%20the%20repression%20unleashed%20by%20the%20Delhi%20and%20UP%20police%20on%20the%20young%20leadership%20that%20was%20protesting%20the%20issue.%20CJP%20had%20taken%20the%20lead%20then%20as%20among%20the%20main%20civil%20and%20legal%20rights%20organisation%20to%20create%20public%20advocacy%20and%20awareness%20of%20the%20dangers%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%202003%20amendment%20to%20the%20Citizenship%20Rules%20(Indian%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%202003)%20that%20present%20the%20danger%20of%20bureaucratic%20profiling%20and%20exclusion%20of%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20Indian%20citizenry%2C%20especially%20unlettered%20and%20marginalized%20Indians.%20CJP%E2%80%99s%20experience%20of%20working%20over%206%20years%20in%20Assam%20(since%202017)%20has%20ensured%20a%20deep%2C%20nuanced%20and%20thorough%20knowledge%20of%20how%20the%20on-ground%20implications%20of%20a%20bureaucracy%20driven%20documentary%20%E2%80%9Ctest%E2%80%9D%20for%20citizens%20means%20denial%20of%20citizenship%20rights%2C%20alienation%20of%20all%20rights%20to%20exist%20in%20terms%20of%20access%20to%20institutions%20and%20welfare%20schemes%2C%20impoverishment%20and%20physical%20and%20mental%20discriminations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EToday%2C%202024%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vibrant%20call%20of%20the%20nationwide%20movement%20was%C2%A0%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EKagaj%20Nehi%20Dikhayenge%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%2C%20i.e.%2C%20we%20shall%20not%20show%20any%20document%20had%20gathered%20momentum%20and%20was%20thus%20silenced.%20CJP%E2%80%99s%20investigation%20has%20shown%20how%2C%20the%20government%20has%20already%20started%20a%20process%20of%20NPR-NRC%20via%20an%20indirect%20another%20route%20which%20required%20no%20documentary%20evidence%20from%20the%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20a%20group%20in%20Metiabruz%2C%20a%20part%20of%20Kolkata%20district%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20close%20collaborators%20with%20CJP%2C%20re-started%20their%20endeavour%20to%20build%20up%20an%20agitation%20to%20resist%20NPR-NRC-CAA.%20They%20opposed%20all%20amendments%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%201955%2C%20which%20vitiated%20our%20constitutional%20right%20to%20citizenship%20by%20birth.%20In%202023%20they%20were%20surprised%20to%20discover%20that%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3EAnnual%20Report%202021-22%20of%20MHA%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0declared%20(in%20section%2015.41%20of%20NPR)%20that%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%202015%2C%20a%20few%20fields%20such%20as%20Name%2C%20Gender%2C%20Date%20and%20Place%20of%20Birth%2C%20Place%20of%20Residence%20and%20Father%E2%80%99s%20and%20Mother%E2%80%99s%20name%20were%20updated%20and%20Aadhaar%2C%20Mobile%20and%20Ration%20Card%20Numbers%20were%20collected%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20But%20neither%20did%20they%20witness%20any%20such%20exercise%20being%20carried%20out%20in%20their%20locality%20from%20the%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%20(RGI)%2C%20nor%20did%20any%20enumerator%20come%20to%20them%20for%20updating%20NPR%20and%20for%20collecting%20Aadhaar%20Number%20in%202015-16.%20So%2C%20this%20event%20led%20them%20to%20file%20a%20series%20of%20RTIs%2C%20First%20Appeals%20and%20Second%20Appeals%20to%20the%20concerned%20government%20authorities%20to%20verify%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20NPR%20process%20starting%20from%202010.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConnecting%20the%20dots%20of%20publicly%20available%20information%20with%20the%20information%20obtained%20through%20RTI%20brings%20out%20a%20compelling%20and%20frightening%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20that%20a%20giant%20step%20towards%20NPR%20and%20NRC%20was%20taken%20quietly%20when%20information%20belonging%20to%20the%20Aadhaar%20database%20was%20linked%20with%20the%20NPR%20database.%20The%20only%20legal%20way%20of%20linking%20the%20two%20databases%20is%20by%20acquiring%C2%A0%3Cb%3Einformed%20consent%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0from%20every%20resident%20through%20an%20exercise%20similar%20to%20the%20Census.%20That%20exercise%20would%20have%20surely%20evoked%20public%20outrage%20similar%20to%20what%20had%20been%20witnessed%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20passing%20of%20CAA%2FCAB.%20However%2C%20it%20seems%20from%20the%20replies%20to%20the%20series%20of%20RTI%20queries%20that%20the%20linking%20was%20done%C2%A0%3Ci%3Ewithout%20any%20informed%20consent.%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0This%20apparently%20illegal%20action%20makes%20the%20NPR%20an%20even%20greater%20threat%20to%20the%20common%20people%20than%20what%20was%20previously%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20developments%20pose%20a%20clear%20and%20present%20danger%20of%20no%20less%20magnitude%20than%20what%20triggered%20the%20CAA-%20NPR-NRC%20movement%2C%20though%20there%20is%20no%20conspicuous%20symbol%20of%20that%20danger%20visible%20to%20the%20public.%20Citizens%20have%20to%20come%20together%20and%20prevent%20governmental%20overreach%20and%20harassment%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcjp.org.in%2Fcjp-exclusive-how-the-union-of-india-took-a-giant-step-towards-both-npr-nrc-in-2015-without-informed-consent%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Citizens%20for%20Justice%20and%20Peace%20website.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708240535000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F22120239%2FMANUU.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhow-the-union-govt-took-a-big-step-towards-npr-nrc-in-2015-without-informed-consent%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20step%20was%20taken%20when%20information%20contained%20in%20the%20Aadhaar%20database%20was%20linked%20with%20the%20NPR%20database%20without%20informed%20consent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhow-the-union-govt-took-a-big-step-towards-npr-nrc-in-2015-without-informed-consent%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20Thailand%20PM%20and%20Manchester%20City%20owner%20freed%20from%20detention%20after%20six%20months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708238700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-thaksin-shinawatra_6459805.jpg%3F20240218064516%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fthaksin-shinawatra-former-thailand-pm-and-manchester-city-owner-freed-from-detention-after-six-months-13074619%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thaksin%20Shinawatra%2C%20the%20convicted%20former%20prime%20minister%20of%20Thailand%2C%20has%20been%20freed%20from%20detention%20after%20spending%20six%20months%20in%20a%20police%20hospital.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fthaksin-shinawatra-former-thailand-pm-and-manchester-city-owner-freed-from-detention-after-six-months-13074619%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fthaksin-shinawatra-former-thailand-pm-and-manchester-city-owner-freed-from-detention-after-six-months-13074619%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fthaksin-shinawatra-former-thailand-pm-and-manchester-city-owner-freed-from-detention-after-six-months-13074619%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stagnant%20Job%20Rate%2C%20Worse%20for%20the%20Educated%3A%20IIM%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29174355%2F20240123_092445.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Researchers%20from%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Management%2C%20IIM%20Lucknow%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20Birla%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20and%20Science%20(BITS)%20Pilani%20and%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20for%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%2C%20have%20found%20%E2%80%9Ca%20stagnating%20employment%20growth%20rate%2C%20weakening%20employment%20elasticity%2C%20slow%20structural%20transformation%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fiim-study-points-to-structural-problems-in-indian-labour-market%2Farticle67857448.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520number%2520of%2520unemployed%2520people%2Cmarket%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520the%2520paper%2520said.%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20has%20reported%20on%20their%20findings%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Journal%20of%20Labour%20Economics%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CJobless%20growth%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20have%20used%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20Office%20(NSSO)%20Employment%20and%20Unemployment%20Survey%20and%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey.%20The%20have%20concluded%20that%20there%20was%20a%20surge%20in%20output%20growth%20and%20employment%20between%201987%E2%80%9388%20and%202004%E2%80%9305%2C%20followed%20by%20%E2%80%98jobless%20growth%E2%80%99%20from%202004%E2%80%9305%20to%202018%E2%80%9319%20and%20a%20very%20small%20%E2%80%9Crebound%E2%80%9D%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CApparently%2C%20economic%20growth%2C%20rather%20than%20creating%20more%20jobs%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20net%20labour%20displacement.%20Alongside%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20important%20to%20examine%20the%20quality%20and%20decency%20of%20jobs%2C%E2%80%9D%20Professor%20S.%20Tripati%20Rao%20of%20IIM%2C%20Lucknow%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%20In%202020%E2%80%9321%2C%20the%20total%20labour%20force%20in%20India%20was%20at%20556.1%20million.%20Of%20this%20a%20majority%20or%2054.9%25%20were%20self-employed%2C%20just%2022.8%25%20in%20regular%20employment%20and%20an%2022.3%25%20in%20casual%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-workforce-not-rising-quality-of-jobs-very-low-cmies-mahesh-vyas%5C%22%3Ereported%20on%20May%202%2C%202023%20on%20the%20crisis%20in%20jobs%20as%20well%20as%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mahesh%20Vyas%20of%20CMIE%20had%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs%20in%20India%20is%20very%20low.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20jobs%20pay%20poorly%20and%20are%20of%20informal%20arrangements%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sectors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20job%20data%20has%20been%20patchy%20and%20not%20revealed%20regularly%20of%20late.%20There%20are%20also%20serious%20questions%20about%20what%20it%20captures%20and%20is%20it%20reflects%20employment%20precarity%20at%20all.%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Fstatistics%2Fjob-quality.htm%5C%22%3EOECD%20uses%20three%20%E2%80%9Cobjective%20and%20measurable%20dimensions%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20to%20help%20quantify%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs%2C%20which%20Indian%20data%20still%20does%20not%20do.%20The%20three%20criteria%20are%2C%20earnings%20quality%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Ccaptures%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20earnings%20contribute%20to%20workers%E2%80%99%20well-being%20in%20terms%20of%20average%20earnings%20and%20their%20distribution%20across%20the%20workforce.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20The%20labour%20market%20security%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20working%20environment%20are%20the%20other%20two%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGender%20disparity%20worsens%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IIM%2FBITS%2FMinistry%20of%20Agriculture%20study%20has%20also%20found%20gender-based%20disparity%20in%20the%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20Rate%20(LFPR)%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20continues%20and%20worryingly%2C%20the%20decline%20of%20LFPR%20is%20higher%20for%20females%20than%20for%20males%20from%201983%20to%202020%E2%80%9321.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20overall%20female%20Work%20Force%20Participation%20Rate%20(WFPR)%20for%20those%20aged%2015%E2%80%9359%20in%202020%E2%80%9321%20stood%20at%2032.46%25%2C%20a%20full%2044.55%20percentage%20points%20below%20that%20of%20men.%20Further%2C%20the%20total%20percentage%20of%20male%20WFPR%20(81.10%25)%20in%20the%20same%20year%20for%20aged%2015%E2%80%9359%20years%20is%20more%20than%20twice%20the%20rate%20for%20female%20adults%20(33.79%25)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20study%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20much%20higher%20for%20highly%20educated%20Indians%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20India%20has%20been%20helping%20mediate%20between%20foreign%20governments%20like%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20more%20controversially%20in%20Israel%2C%20for%20providing%20semi-skilled%20and%20unskilled%20labour%20to%20those%20countries%2C%20signalling%20its%20inability%20to%20provide%20jobs%20in%20basic%20manufacturing%20industries%20in%20the%20country.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Ftaiwan-agrees-bring-indian-migrant-workers-ease-job-crunch-2024-02-16%2F%5C%22%3EMoU%20with%20Taiwan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20this%20respect%20was%20signed%20on%20February%2016%2C%202024.%20The%20jobs%20crisis%20in%20India%2C%20as%20per%20the%20BBC%E2%80%99s%20report%20last%20month%2C%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-68027582%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cdriving%20workers%20to%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20even%20before%20the%20war%20on%20Gaza%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20India%20had%20%E2%80%9Csigned%20an%20agreement%20in%20May%202023%20that%20would%20send%2042%2C000%20Indian%20construction%20and%20nursing%20workers%20to%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20comments%20by%20former%20Israeli%20foreign%20minister%20Eli%20Cohen%20in%20the%20Israeli%20Knesset%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fisrael-conducts-recruitment-drive-in-uttar-pradesh-haryana-as-bar-on-gaza-palestinians-workers-caused-labour-shortage-11706146837290.html%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20%3Cem%3EMint.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20prospects%20for%20employment%20do%20not%20improve%20with%20rising%20education%20levels%20and%20progressively%20get%20worse%2C%20also%20as%20per%20this%20study%2C%20suggesting%20a%20comprehensive%20failure%20to%20generate%20jobs%20across%20the%20board%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20India%20rises%20with%20education%20levels.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20illiterate%20and%20less%20educated%20class%20(below%20primary)%20was%200.57%25%20and%201.13%25%20respectively%20while%2C%20for%20the%20highly%20educated%20class%20(graduates%20and%20above)%2C%20it%20was%2014.73%25%20in%202020%E2%80%9321%20for%20the%20age%20group%2015%E2%80%9329%20years.%E2%80%9D%20This%20pattern%20can%20be%20seen%20across%20the%20years%2C%20as%20per%20the%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20recommends%20more%20attention%20to%20MNREGA%2C%20other%20poverty%20alleviation%20programmes%20and%20public%20works.%20It%20finds%20MNREGA%20to%20positively%20help%20with%20%E2%80%9Craising%20wages%20in%20rural%20areas%20by%205%25%2C%20increase%20in%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20among%20female%20workers%2C%20improvement%20in%20low-caste%20working%20bargaining%20power%2C%20increasing%20rural%20wage%20levels%2C%20and%20fall%20in%20reliance%20on%20high-caste%20employers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708238575000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29174355%2F20240123_092445.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fstagnant-job-rate-worse-for-the-educated-iim-study%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20study%20by%20IIM%2C%20BITS%20(Pilani)%20and%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%20finds%20that%20India%20is%20not%20generating%20enough%20jobs.%20The%20gender%20disparity%20is%20sticky%20and%20while%20there%20is%20a%20jobs%20crisis%20also%20for%20unskilled%20labour%2C%20proportionately%20there%20are%20far%20fewer%20jobs%20for%20the%20better%20educated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fstagnant-job-rate-worse-for-the-educated-iim-study%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ayodhya%20Gets%20a%20Makeover%20%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20160746%2Fimage-1778.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%201812%2C%20having%20successfully%20chased%20away%20Napoleon%E2%80%99s%20armies%2C%20Russian%20Czar%20Alexander%20the%20First%20decided%20to%20construct%20a%20grand%20temple%20for%20Christ%20in%20Moscow%20by%20way%20of%20thanksgiving.%20With%20the%20completion%20of%20the%20magnificent%20temple%20to%20Christ%20the%20Saviour%2C%20Moscow%20became%20the%20third%20Rome%20for%20the%20Russian%20public%2C%20writes%20Psakov%2C%20a%20sage%20and%20visionary.%20The%20holy%20temple%20project%20took%2045%20years%20to%20complete.%20It%20was%20consecrated%20in%20May%201883%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20then%20czar%2C%20Alexander%20the%20Third%2C%20as%20a%20timeless%20sacred%20spot.%20It%20was%20a%20really%20%3Cem%3Edivya%20bhavya%3C%2Fem%3E%20piece%20of%20art%2C%20more%20than%2030%20stories%20tall%20with%20walls%20covered%20with%20frescos%2C%20a%20giant%20iconostasis%20that%20used%20422%20kilos%20of%20gold%2C%20and%20a%20main%20bell%20weighing%2024%20tonnes.%20Its%20interior%20was%20dazzling%20with%20gold%20silver%20and%20gems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20goddess%20of%20history%20it%20seems%2C%20had%20her%20own%20plans.%20The%20Bolshevik%20Revolution%20happened%20in%201917%2C%20the%20czar%20and%20his%20family%20were%20exiled%20and%20then%20killed.%20And%20then%20in%201931%20the%20all-powerful%20leader%20Stalin%20decided%20to%20raze%20it%20and%20erase%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20temple%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20376px)%2085vw%2C%20376px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mrinal%20Pande%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22376%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783.jpg%20525w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783-246x300.jpg%20246w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-642789%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOvernight%20the%20temple%20was%20made%20out%20of%20bounds%2C%20surrounded%20by%20barbed%20wire.%20When%20the%20demolishers%20had%20done%20whatever%20they%20could%2C%20only%20the%20shell%20remained%20of%20the%20once%20magnificent%20temple.%20All%20gold%20and%20gems%20and%20silk%20and%20velvet%20vestments%20embroidered%20with%20gold%20and%20silver%20threads%20were%20removed%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cycle%20of%20erection%20and%20after%20some%20time%20shattering%20of%20grand%20places%20of%20worship%20and%20then%20again%20their%20re-erection%20has%20a%20long%20history%20in%20the%20world.%20Ayodhya%2C%20the%20latest%20city%20to%20be%20re-energised%20by%20the%20building%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20too%20has%20been%20through%20this%20cycle.%20Today%20few%20know%20that%20the%20holy%20site%20even%20pre-dates%20Ram.%20The%20Atharva%20Veda%20(second%20chapter)%20calls%20Ayodhya%20by%20its%20earlier%20Buddhist%20name%2C%20Saket.%20Buddhist%20text%20Divyavadaan%20corroborates%20this%20and%20says%20that%20Saket%20%C2%A0created%20itself%20(%3Cem%3ESvayamagata%2C%20swayamagata%20Saket%20iti%20uchyate%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ancient%20folklore%2C%20the%20city%20that%20King%20Dashrath%20had%20built%20was%20buried%20under%20Sita%E2%80%99s%20curse.%20Several%20centuries%20later%20it%20was%20rediscovered%20by%20King%20Vikramaditya%20through%20a%20dream%20wherein%20the%20goddess%20of%20the%20city%20requested%20him%20to%20unearth%20her%20city.%20The%20king%20had%20it%20dug%20out%20from%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20earth.%20%C2%A0The%20vast%20pan-Indian%20popularity%20of%20the%20cult%20of%20Ram%20and%20Ayodhya%20as%20his%20holy%20birth%20place%20began%20only%20in%20the%2014th%20century%20with%20the%20Bhakti%20movement%20and%20its%20arrival%20up%20north%20in%20latter%20half%20of%2016th%3Cspan%3E%20century%3C%2Fspan%3E%20CE.%20Thereafter%20the%20Vaishnavite%20Ramanand%20sect%20and%20saint%20poet%20Tulsidas%20popularised%20it%20by%20their%20devotional%20poetry%20that%20portrayed%20Lord%20Ram%20of%20Ayodhya%20as%20the%20ideal%20Man-God%20(%3Cem%3EMaya%20Manushyam%20Hari%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Linking%20this%20with%20the%20recent%20makeover%20of%20Ayodhya%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20and%20its%20formal%20installation%20of%20an%20idol%20of%20Ram%20as%20a%20young%20boy%20on%20January%2022%20is%20actually%20a%20journey%20into%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20an%20area%20as%20a%20holy%20spot%20and%20building%20and%20rebuilding%20monuments%20needs%20clever%20negotiators%20and%20publicists.%20So%20after%20the%20Ram%20cult%20got%20going%2C%20Hanumangarhi%2C%20the%20fortress%20of%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20emissary%2C%20came%20up%20and%20by%20the%2018th%20century%20became%20the%20natural%20meeting%20place%20for%20representatives%20of%20a%20slowly%20dying%20monarchy%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20empowered%20Awadh%20Durbar%20and%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20officials.%20All%20made%20important%20power-sharing%20deals%20with%20local%20mercenaries%20and%20bands%20of%20armed%20%3Cem%3Esadhus%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22In%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20Hailing%2C%20Sita%20Was%20Forgotten.%20Her%20Revival%20Would%20Have%20Symbolised%20Healing%20for%20Men%20and%20Women%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fin-rams-hailing-sita-was-forgotten-her-revival-would-have-symbolised-healing-for-men-and-women%5C%22%3EIn%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20Hailing%2C%20Sita%20Was%20Forgotten.%20Her%20Revival%20Would%20Have%20Symbolised%20Healing%20for%20Men%20and%20Women%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20rebuilding%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20at%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20birthplace%20began%20as%20an%20idea%20with%20immense%20political%20potential%20in%201992%2C%20the%20year%20of%20razing%20of%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20said%20to%20have%20been%20built%20by%20a%20general%2C%20Mir%20Baki%2C%20who%20had%20replaced%20an%20existing%20temple%20to%20build%20a%20mosque%20named%20after%20the%20victorious%20Mughal%20king%20Babar.%20Since%201992%2C%20Ayodhya%20became%20a%20political%20petridish%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20The%20mega%202019%20victory%20in%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20rhetoric%20turned%20towards%20erecting%20a%20%3Cem%3Ebhavya%2C%20navya%2C%20divya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(grand%2C%20new%20and%20holy)%20temple%20there%20to%20Ram%2C%20both%20by%20way%20of%20thanksgiving%20and%20declaring%20the%20imminent%20arrival%20of%20a%20Hindutva-driven%20state.%20Soon%20it%20got%20the%20necessary%20judicial%20green%20signal%20to%20go%20ahead.%20Work%20was%20then%20speeded%20up%20to%20try%20and%20coincide%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20temple%20in%20January%202024%20with%20general%20election%20rallies%20scheduled%20just%20a%20few%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20aided%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%2C%20led%20everything%20from%20the%20front%20and%20at%20the%20installation%20ceremony%20of%20the%20Balak%20Ram%20statue%2C%20it%20was%20announced%20that%20Ram%20Lalla%20has%20returned%20after%20500%20years%20to%20his%20rightful%20place.%20As%20conch%20shells%20sounded%20and%20a%20thousand%20throats%20sang%20%3Cem%3Ebhajans%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20was%20repeated%20again%20and%20again%20that%20Hindutva%20was%20the%20future%20and%20the%20core%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20would%20draw%20thousands%20of%20pilgrims%20from%20not%20just%20India%20but%20also%20foreign%20lands%20where%20diaspora%20Hindus%20still%20follow%20Hindutva.%20It%20was%20also%20underscored%20forcefully%20how%20this%20would%20invite%20capital%20investment%20in%20the%20state%20and%20Ayodhya%20in%20particular%20and%20generate%20jobs%20and%20opportunities%20for%20entrepreneurs%20and%20the%20tourist%20industry%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20who%20hail%20from%20Uttarakhand%2C%20recently%20christened%20Dev%20Bhumi%2C%20learnt%20early%20on%20how%20this%20works.%20The%20new%20pilgrims%20are%20religious%20tourists.%20The%20pilgrims%20had%20been%20coming%20to%20Ayodhya%20even%20earlier%2C%20but%20they%20were%20mostly%20simple%20rural%20folk%20or%20a%20few%20old%20couples%20with%20limited%20spending%20power%20and%20not%20much%20interest%20in%20worldly%20pursuits.%20The%20new%20tourists%20are%20young%20and%20will%20visit%20round%20the%20year%20in%20droves%20provided%20that%20pilgrimage%20trails%20have%20been%20made%20user%20friendly.%20No%20more%20smelly%20dharmshalas%20with%20bed%20bugs%20and%20bad%20food%20and%20temperamental%20Pandas%20for%20them.%20Photos%20of%20hotels%20and%20home%20stays%2C%20spas%20and%20food%20courts%20all%20along%20the%20routes%20must%20be%20available%20online%20for%20%E2%80%98customers%E2%80%99%20before%20the%20group%20bookings%20begin.%20And%20yes%2C%20it%20will%20bring%20in%20heap%20big%20bucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20new%20species%20of%20pilgrims%20has%20also%20changed%20religion%20into%20an%20industry%20that%20follows%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20algorithms%20keenly%20and%20creates%20bespoke%20exclusive%20packages.%20Old-style%20darshan%20and%20immersion%20in%20holy%20rivers%20are%20pass%C3%A9.%20The%20bespoke%20packages%20promise%20you%20%E2%80%9Ca%20mystic%20experience%20of%20a%20temple%2Fcity%20old-as-time!%E2%80%9D%20along%20with%20chances%20to%20do%20a%20bit%20of%20river%20rafting%20and%20air%20diving.%20The%20tourism%20promoters%20hand%20you%20addresses%20and%20coupons%20for%20buying%20souvenirs%20and%20holy%20waters%20and%20%3Cem%3Eprasadam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20send%20you%20maps%20dotted%20with%20selfie%20points.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20should%20the%20customers%20so%20wish%2C%20there%20will%20be%20camera%20crew%20available%20to%20capture%20the%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20waggish%20ego.%20Honoured%20pilgrim%2Ftourists%20face%20none%20of%20the%20earlier%20multiple%20checkings%20by%20petty%20officials%20or%20long%20waits%20at%20toll%20plazas.%20Difficulties%2C%20as%20and%20when%20they%20arise%2C%20can%20be%20easily%20negotiated%20with%20some%20exchange%20of%20money%20and%20flashing%20official%20(read%20party)%20badges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22When%20Ravan%20Triumphs%20in%20Ayodhya%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwhen-ravan-triumphs-in-ayodhya%5C%22%3EWhen%20Ravan%20Triumphs%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20is%20still%20out%20on%20whether%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20and%20sundry%20others%20who%20have%20already%20bought%20properties%20to%20go%20live%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20will%20actually%20stay%20there.%20But%20the%20millennial%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20progress%20in%20the%20age%20of%20global%20meltdowns%2C%20works%20along%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20Amritkaal%20economy%20that%20has%20hard-wired%20them%20for%20planning%20for%20the%20coming%20year%20as%20they%20don%20their%20itinerant%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20robes%20and%20get%20into%20their%20SUVs%20or%20leave%20for%20the%20newly%20built%20airport.%20Damn%20the%20carbon%20footprints%20or%20local%20water%20shortages%20that%20are%20routine%20now%20in%20temple%20towns.%20The%20neo-converts%20to%20Hindutva%3A%20scientists%20and%20engineers%2C%20doctors%2C%20IT%20czars%20and%20environmentalists%2C%20both%20desi%20and%20NRI%2C%20are%20all%20happy%20singing%20and%20partying%20to%20pop%20bhajans.%20The%20built%20in%20obsolescence%20within%20such%20tourism%20models%20does%20not%20interest%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Uttarakhand%2C%20we%20see%20the%20results%20clearly.%20As%20more%20and%20more%20pilgrims%20flock%20to%20Gangotri%20and%20Yamunotri%2C%20the%20glaciers%C2%A0%20recede.%20The%20broader%20the%20roads%2C%20the%20bigger%20the%20landslides%20during%20monsoons.%20Snow%20has%20already%20thinned%20to%20a%20stop%20in%20the%20entire%20Himalayan%20region.%20So%20watch%20out%2C%20Ayodhya%3B%20if%20you%20do%20not%20watch%20out%2C%20the%20place%20will%20lose%20its%20endearing%C2%A0%20informality%20and%20become%20another%20industrial%20city%20inviting%20skyscrapers%2C%20vast%20traffic%20jams%20and%20malls%20with%20food%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverybody%20knows%20this%2C%20but%20we%20are%20still%20witnessing%20the%20genetic%20inability%20of%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20powerful%20to%20deny%20the%20alarming%20reality%20of%20global%20warming.%20Inaugurating%20the%20first%20grand%20Hindu%20temple%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20built%20by%20the%20BAPS%20(Swamin%20Narayan%20sect)%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20described%20himself%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpriest%20of%20Ma%20Bharati%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20added%20how%20the%20grand%20temple%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20has%20enhanced%20Ayodhya%20joy.%20The%20BAPS%2C%20he%20predicted%2C%20will%20be%20a%20centre%20of%20communal%20harmony%20and%20global%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20about%20as%20good%20as%20it%20is%20going%20to%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaakhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Sunday%20column%20from%20Mrinal%20Pande%2C%20in%20which%20she%20writes%20of%20what%20she%20sees%20and%20also%20participates%20in.%20That%20has%20been%20her%20burden%20to%20bear%20ever%20since%20she%20embarked%20on%20a%20life%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20writer%2C%20editor%2C%20author%20and%20as%20chairperson%20of%20Prasar%20Bharti.%20Her%20journey%20of%20being%20a%20witness-participant%20continues.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708236243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20160746%2Fimage-1778.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fayodhya-gets-a-makeover%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20species%20of%20pilgrims%20has%20changed%20religion%20into%20an%20industry%20that%20follows%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20algorithms%20keenly%20and%20creates%20bespoke%20exclusive%20packages.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fayodhya-gets-a-makeover%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commission%20Will%20Follow%20Supreme%20Court's%20Directions%20on%20Electoral%20Bonds%3A%20CEC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25220532%2FScreenshot-2023-10-25-at-10.04.47%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EChief%20election%20commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20has%20said%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20will%20follow%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20directions%20on%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20official%20body%20to%20comment%20on%20following%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20calling%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20unconstitutional%2C%20and%20asking%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20reveal%20details%20of%20all%20the%20donors%20who%20used%20the%20opaque%20scheme.%20The%20finance%20ministry%20and%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20%E2%80%93%20both%20of%20which%20had%20key%20roles%20in%20drafting%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20have%20said%20nothing%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20its%20affidavit%20to%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20it%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20transparency%20and%20when%20the%20order%20is%20issued%2C%20it%20will%20take%20action%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kumar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Felection-commission-to-follow-top-court-order-on-electoral-bonds-cec-rajiv-kumar-101708184521890.html%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20Saturday%20(February%2017)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20EC%20had%20taken%20contradictory%20positions%20on%20the%20schemes%20at%20different%20times.%20While%20it%20had%20expressed%20serious%20reservations%20initially%2C%20even%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cretrograde%20step%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20then%20went%20on%20to%20back%20the%20scheme%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20argue%20that%20it%20should%20not%20be%20stayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20response%20from%20the%20Modi%20government%20%E2%80%93%20which%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%5C%22%3Evehemently%20argued%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20so%20far%20has%20come%20from%20Union%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Meghwal.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20government%20is%20%E2%80%9Cexamining%E2%80%9D%20the%20verdict%20and%20will%20decide%20whether%20to%20challenge%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EBJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%20The%20Trinamool%20Congress%20has%20received%20Rs%201%2C096%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708233793000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25220532%2FScreenshot-2023-10-25-at-10.04.47%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-will-follow-supreme-courts-directions-on-electoral-bonds-cec%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIn%20its%20affidavit%20to%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20it%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20transparency%20and%20when%20the%20order%20is%20issued%2C%20it%20will%20take%20action%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%26quot%3B%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-will-follow-supreme-courts-directions-on-electoral-bonds-cec%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Difficult%20Conversations%20Await%20the%20INDIA%20Alliance%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18101256%2Findia-jandk.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20National%20Conference%20(NC)%20president%20Farooq%20Abdullah%20has%20thrown%20down%20a%20gauntlet%20with%20his%20remarks%20on%20seat-sharing%20arrangements%20with%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20for%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20reporters%20in%20Srinagar%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2015%2C%20Abdullah%20said%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9Cno%20two%20opinions%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20NC%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20was%20going%20to%20contest%20the%202024%20general%20election%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%9Con%20the%20basis%20of%20our%20strength%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20remarks%20triggered%20speculations%20that%20after%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20the%20NC%20president%20could%20be%20the%20latest%20addition%20to%20the%20list%20of%20political%20leaders%20who%20have%20deserted%20the%20fledgling%20INDIA%20alliance%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmar%20Abdullah%2C%20the%20NC%20vice-president%2C%20however%2C%20clarified%20that%20his%20party%20%E2%80%9Ccontinues%20to%20remain%20a%20member%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%E2%80%9D.%20He%20claimed%20that%20the%20NC%20has%20had%20%E2%80%9Cinformal%20talks%E2%80%9D%20on%20seat-sharing%20with%20the%20Congress%2C%20which%20leads%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20while%20asserting%20that%20his%20party%20was%20going%20to%20contest%20on%20three%20out%20of%20six%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20Ladakh%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20constituencies%20%E2%80%93%20Srinagar-Budgam%2C%20Baramulla-Kupwara%20and%20Anantnag-Rajouri%20%E2%80%93%20were%20won%20by%20the%20NC%20in%20the%202019%20parliamentary%20election.%20%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20the%20seats%20that%20are%20to%20be%20discussed%20are%20those%20held%20by%20the%20BJP%20(Jammu%2C%20Udhampur%20and%20Ladakh).%20We%20are%20firm%20on%20that%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20Omar%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20parliamentary%20constituencies%20are%20spread%20over%2012%20districts%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20valley%20and%20Pir%20Panjal%20region%20where%20all%20the%20three%20major%20constituents%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20NC%20and%20the%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20have%20had%20a%20significant%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202014%20assembly%20election%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20the%20PDP%20had%20emerged%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20with%2028%20seats%20(including%20three%20seats%20in%20the%20Pir%20Panjal%20region%20and%20the%20rest%20from%20Kashmir%20Valley)%20followed%20by%20the%20National%20Conference%20with%2015%20seats%20and%20the%20Congress%20with%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu-based%20editor%20and%20political%20analyst%20Zafar%20Choudhary%20said%20that%20the%20NC%E2%80%99s%20decision%20was%20unlikely%20to%20be%20acceptable%20to%20the%20allies%20of%20INDIA%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20PDP%20and%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20force%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfight%20to%20the%20finish%E2%80%9D%20between%20the%20three%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20BJP%20looks%20confident%20on%20its%20two%20traditional%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20(Jammu%20and%20Udhampur)%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20NC-PDP-Congress%20alliance%20would%20clearly%20put%20the%20BJP%20in%20a%20position%20of%20advantage%20in%20Anantnag-Rajouri%20and%20Ladakh%20seats.%20An%20unofficial%20BJP%20ally%20could%20even%20emerge%20as%20a%20key%20competitor%20in%20north%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20Choudhary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERekha%20Chowdhary%2C%20former%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Jammu%2C%20believes%20that%20the%20NC%20is%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbetter%20position%E2%80%9D%20electorally%20in%20Kashmir%20than%20other%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20main%20rival%20of%20the%20National%20Conference%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20which%20is%20the%20PDP%2C%20has%20become%20quite%20weak%20because%20of%20the%20exodus%20of%20some%20of%20its%20leaders%20and%20other%20factors.%20The%20PDP%20has%20lost%20its%20confidence%20and%20the%20party%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20where%20it%20can%20negotiate%20seat-sharing%20with%20other%20INDIA%20partners%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZafar%20Choudhary%20agreed%20that%20the%20PDP%20has%20been%20suffering%20politically%20because%20of%20its%20alliance%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%202015.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20subsequent%20events%20including%20government%20formation%20crisis%20following%20Mufti%20Sayeed%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%202016%20civilian%20unrest%2C%20fall%20of%20government%20in%202018%20and%20the%20casual%20handling%20of%20the%20dismissal%20of%20assembly%20project%20the%20PDP%20in%20a%20poor%20light%20and%2C%20consequently%2C%20the%20NC%20in%20a%20better%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20senior%20PDP%20leader%20said%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20question%E2%80%9D%20that%20his%20party%20was%20going%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20contest%20but%20%E2%80%9Cour%20foremost%20goal%20is%20unity%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20party%20was%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconsultation%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20won%E2%80%99t%20take%20a%20decision%20under%20pressure%20or%20in%20a%20hurry%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20question%20of%20just%20the%20elections%20but%20how%20to%20strengthen%20our%20voice%20at%20the%20national%20level%20and%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20PDP%20leader%2C%20who%20served%20as%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20PDP-BJP%20coalition%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PDP%20leader%20said%20that%20the%20party%20will%20%E2%80%9Cideally%20want%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20a%20united%20voice%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20BJP%20from%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20if%20one%20of%20the%20constituents%20does%20not%20want%20to%20yield%20space%20to%20others%2C%20we%20would%20feel%20our%20attempts%20from%202019%20to%20forge%20unity%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20first%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Gupkar%20Alliance%20and%20then%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20have%20failed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZafar%20Choudhary%20said%20that%20the%20Gupkar%20alliance%20between%20the%20three%20parties%20did%20not%20work%20electorally%20as%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%202020%20District%20Development%20Council%20(DDC)%20elections%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20parties%20also%20realised%20that%20they%20compete%20on%20the%20same%20electoral%20landscape%20for%20their%20individual%20survival%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20then%2C%20Omar%20has%20believed%20in%20separating%20the%20electoral%20and%20ideological%20agenda%20within%20the%20Gupkar%20alliance.%20In%20November%202022%2C%20the%20NC%20released%20a%20list%20of%2046%20leaders%20for%20as%20many%20constituencies%20in%20Kashmir%20calling%20them%20Constituency-Incharge.%20This%20was%20a%20clear%20message%20to%20the%20allies%20that%20there%20was%20no%20scope%20for%20alliance%20whenever%20assembly%20elections%20are%20held.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20Dr%20Abdullah%20and%20Omar%20have%20%E2%80%9Cconsistently%20held%20divergent%20views%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20alliance%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20Dr%20Abdullah%20has%20always%20reiterated%20the%20primacy%20of%20the%20Gupkar%20Alliance%2C%20Omar%20has%20taken%20more%20practical%20actions%20to%20consolidate%20on%20a%20post-2019%20advantage%20uniquely%20available%20to%20the%20National%20Conference.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERekha%20Chowdharyy%20said%20that%20the%20NC%E2%80%99s%20performance%20in%20the%20DDC%20election%20may%20have%20contributed%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cconfidence%E2%80%9D%20about%20its%20performance%20in%20the%20upcoming%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20commitment%20(to%20INDIA%20alliance)%20is%20not%20entrenched%20in%20the%20political%20parties%20in%20Kashmir.%20No%20party%20will%20sacrifice%20its%20interests%20for%20the%20interests%20of%20any%20alliance.%20While%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%20is%20more%20committed%20to%20the%20INDIA%20and%20Gupkar%20alliances%20for%20the%20survival%20of%20her%20party%2C%20NC%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20either%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20media%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20Omar%2